subject: Add GET method for TriggerCollection
commitMessage:
Add GET method for TriggerCollection

Added GET method for retrieving list of Triggers from Telemetry service

Tested:
- Added single Trigger and requested result from bmcweb via
  /redfish/v1/TelemetryService/Triggers
- Added multiple Triggers numeric and discrete, and requested results
  from bmcweb via /redfish/v1/TelemetryService/Triggers
- Verified uri /redfish/v1/TelemetryService/Triggers by using
  Redfish-Service-Validator with no Triggers/empty Collection (passed)

Signed-off-by: Lukasz Kazmierczak <lukasz.kazmierczak@intel.com>
Change-Id: Ide00eb44901ea1b97b80fc5c5ddfd97e393d4a04

Unfortunately, for Telemetry Reports and Triggers we must use our version of 'getCollection' (this one here). I have tried to use function call you had suggested but it didn't work in every case. For example in Telemetry there can be no Reports and no Triggers, then our 'getCollection' will recognize error from dbus enquiry -> boost::system::errc::io_error, as 'objects not found' and provide empty members array with 'members.count = 0' data. For the same case your version of 'getCollection' will process io_error as any other error and respond with internal error notification, giving no substantial (and expected by Telemetry) JSON data in return. Please take that into account and reconsider.
